mber screens and buttons would be an attractive addition to any office desk, kitchen counter or bedroom end table.","This line of Uniden phones gives you sturdy handsets and considerable ease of use. One model in particular, the Uniden D1780-4, comes with a base station and accompanying handset as well as three other identical handsets.","If you choose, you can purchase more handsets up to an impressive 12 altogether, which should outfit just about any home or business.","One thing you do not get with this otherwise helpful model is Bluetooth capability. For businesses or homes filled with people for whom cellphones are as essential as air, this might be a drawback big enough for them to eschew this model. (In that case, Uniden offers link-to-cell models in another line, including the Uniden D1780-4B model, which offers the same number of headsets.)","However, not everyone is attuned to the switch-between-cell-and-home-phone approach, so the more straightforward functionality of the Uniden D1780-4 might make it the best cordless phone system for their needs.","This cordless phone includes seven hours of talk time, which is relatively short, but provides a healthy seven days&#39; worth of battery life. You get 14 minutes for the recorded messages you might receive, and the handsets have speakerphones.","The built-in phonebook can handle 100 entries, and the caller ID holds 50 entries. You can set different ringtones for different handsets and silence a particular handset if you do not want it to ring in a particular room.","With the Uniden D1780-4, you also get conferencing capabilities, an alarm, a headset jack and an intercom system."]},"id":"eda38f58-ef6f-4552-883b-3450fada463b","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"a723323f-3d86-411d-bdb6-c5ad0d618b39","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["There is no Bluetooth capability, which could be a problem for some consumers, but not necessarily for everyone. The Uniden D1780-4 does furnish you with traditio